{
  "stem": "8775.3",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And there was absolutely no sanitation facilities, nothing at all.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And that's how we were there.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And lots of times, Germans said they wanted volunteers.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "My mom would never let me go out from her sight and volunteer.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And then we suddenly heard that the Russians are coming in from both directions, from Dresden and from Prague.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And we were liberated one day after the war ended, on May 9th, 1945, by Russian troops.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And of course, some people-- for some people, it wasn't the end.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "Some people died even afterwards because of the food which was distributed by the Russian army, the heavy bread.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And their weakened stomach just couldn't digest it, couldn't take it.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And I guess my mother and I were fairly fortunate that we were among those who survived it.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And as a matter of fact, we had some friends going to Theresienstadt and they saw the names of the people who were in the barracks and our names was listed there as being survived, because the ones who did not survive I think there was an asterisk next to their names.",
      "word_count": 52
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And we had to wait until clearance, until everything was cleared.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And we had to be sanitized, of course.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "And we had to wait for a transport to take us back to Hungary.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Theresienstadt, well, we were liberated on May 9th.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I think towards the end of the July it took about at least two and a half, three months to get us back to the transport and transport taking us back to Budapest.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And in Budapest, there was a national committee for the caring of the deportees, the Jewish committee.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they had a reception for us.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They took us into their offices.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
